dc_title_s: Part of the south coast of Arabia from a survey by Captain Haines, Indian Navy, and the officers of the Palinurus, 1839
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Offshore shoals and banks are shown. Includes inset map: Plan of Aden [scale ca. 1:159,600]. Built areas, remains of an aqueduct, and seasonal variation in shoreline are shown. Settlements and tribal territories are shown. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 9 (1839), pp. 125-56; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v. 9 1839.
dc_publisher_s: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1839.
